<!Doctype>
<html>
<head>
    <style>
    html, body, figure, p {
        margin:0;
        border: 0;
        padding: 0;
        font-family:sans-serif;
    }
    body{
        padding:50px;
        margin:auto;
        background: grey;

    }
    .group:after{
        display: block;
        content:"";
        clear: both;
    }

    .left figure{
        height: 200px;
        width: 200px;
    }

    .left img{
        width: 80%;
        height: 80%;
        vertical-align:center;
        margin-top:30%;
        margin-left:30%;
        border: 8px solid grey;
        border-radius:100px;
        margin-right: 0;
    }
    .right p{
        color: grey;
        line-height: 150%;
        font-size: 20px;
        margin-bottom:20px;
        padding-left:0;
        padding-right:60px;
    }
    .left{
        float:left;
        width:30%;
        margin-right:0;
        padding-right: 0;
    }
    .right{
        width: 65%;
        float: right;

    }
    .box{
        background: -webkit-radial-gradient(white, #D8D8D8, #BDBDBD);
        background: -o-radial-gradient(white, #D8D8D8, #BDBDBD);
        background: -moz-radial-gradient(white, #D8D8D8, #BDBDBD);
        background: radial-gradient(white, #D8D8D8, #BDBDBD);


        margin-left:8%;
        margin-right:8%;
        margin-top:0%;

        border-radius:250px;
        padding:60px 10px;
        overflow:hidden;
        box-shadow: 0 0 200px black;
    }

    @media screen and (max-width: 600px){
        .left{
            display:none;
        }
        .box{
            border-radius:0;
            padding:0;
            margin:0;
            size:10px;
        }
        .right{
            width:100%;
        }
        .right p{
            font-size: 10px;
            padding:15px 5px;
        }
    }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="box group">
        <div class="left">
        <figure >
           <img src="<%= asset_path 'ling2.jpg' %>">
        </figure>
        </div>

    <div class="right">
    <p class="one">
        Hello, I am Ling. Welcome to my portfolio site!
    </p>
    <p class="two">
        I enjoy creating an amazing world with my code. The tools I am currently using are Javascript, jQuery, CSS3, HTML5, Ruby on Rails. And I am always eager to learn new technologies.
    </p>

<p class="three">
        I love web development like a handyman loves fixing up houses. And I want to join a fast-growing team to allow my coding to reach more people. If your team is expanding and you are looking for a helpful front-end developer with hands-on experience in building web apps, let's talk.
    </p>
    </div>

    </div>
</body>
</html>